gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 121, Trail Blazers 118
gameRecap.excerpt: The Kings defeated the Trail Blazers, 121-118, in overtime. Domantas Sabonis recorded 27 points (11-14 FG), 11 rebounds and nine assists for the Kings, while Malik Monk added 23 points, six rebounds and a career-high 10 assists in the victory. Jerami Grant led all scorers with 38 points (5-8 3PM), along with nine rebounds and five assists for the Trail Blazers in the losing effort. The Kings improve to 3-4 on the season, while the Trail Blazers fall to 3-5.
